        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Window handle type</para>
<para>This identified the windowing system and protocol that the window needs to use. This also selects which member of the <ref refid="structvout__window__t_1a2c9e8c53ee2e63dafc817351fa3c9846" kindref="member">handle</ref> union and the <ref refid="structvout__window__t_1aff7f867d17f5c3395a8fe8a785ab8311" kindref="member">display</ref> union are to be set.</para>
<para>The possible values are defined in <ref refid="group__video__window_1ga61d87f40cd3e2165ead8e755febbc403" kindref="member">vout_window_type</ref>.</para>
<para>VOUT_WINDOW_TYPE_INVALID is a special placeholder type. It means that any windowing system is acceptable. In that case, the plugin must set its actual type during activation. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
