    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Graphical window</para>
<para>This structure is an abstract interface to the windowing system. The window is normally used to draw video (and subpictures) into, but it can also be used for other purpose (e.g. OpenGL visualization).</para>
<para>The window is responsible for providing a window handle, whose exact meaning depends on the windowing system. It also must report some events such as user input (keyboard, mouse) and window resize.</para>
<para>Finally, it must support some control requests such as for fullscreen mode. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
